      */
    }
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "starting"
    }}>{`Starting`}</h2>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "command"
    }}>{`Command`}</h3>
    <Tabs block={false} centered={true} groupId="interfaces" placeholder="How did you install Vector?" select={true} size={null} values={[{
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "DPKG",
      "value": "dpkg"
    }, {
      "group": "Platforms",
      "label": "Docker CLI",
      "value": "docker-cli"
    }, {
      "group": "Platforms",
      "label": "Docker Compose",
      "value": "docker-compose"
    }, {
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "Homebrew",
      "value": "homebrew"
    }, {
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "MSI",
      "value": "msi"
    }, {
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "Nix",
      "value": "nix"
    }, {
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "RPM",
      "value": "rpm"
    }, {
      "group": "Nones",
      "label": "Vector CLI",
      "value": "vector-cli"
    }]} mdxType="Tabs">
      <TabItem value="dpkg" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{`sudo systemctl start vector
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="docker-cli" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{`docker run \\
  -v $PWD/vector.toml:/etc/vector/vector.toml:ro \\
  timberio/vector:latest-alpine
`}</code></pre>
        <CodeExplanation mdxType="CodeExplanation">
          <ul>
            <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`-v $PWD/vector.to...`}</inlineCode>{` flag passes your custom configuration to Vector.`}</li>
            <li parentName="ul">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`timberio/vector:latest-alpine`}</inlineCode>{` is the default image we've chosen, you are welcome to use `}<a parentName="li" {...{
                "href": "/docs/setup/installation/platforms/docker/#variants"
              }}>{`other image variants`}</a>{`.`}</li>
          </ul>
        </CodeExplanation>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="docker-compose" mdxType="TabItem">
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="homebrew" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{`brew services start vector
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="msi" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bat"
          }}>{`.\\bin\\vector --config config\\vector.toml
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="nix" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{`vector --config /etc/vector/vector.toml
`}</code></pre>
        <CodeExplanation mdxType="CodeExplanation">
          <ul>
            <li parentName="ul"><inlineCode parentName="li">{`vector`}</inlineCode>{` is placed in your `}<inlineCode parentName="li">{`$PATH`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</li>
            <li parentName="ul">{`You must create a `}<a parentName="li" {...{
                "href": "/docs/setup/configuration/"
              }}>{`Vector configuration file`}</a>{` to
successfully start Vector.`}</li>
          </ul>
        </CodeExplanation>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="rpm" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{`sudo systemctl start vector
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="vector-cli" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{`vector --config vector.toml
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
    </Tabs>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "flags"
    }}>{`Flags`}</h3>
    <table>
      <thead parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="thead">
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Flag`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Description`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}></th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}><strong parentName="td">{`Required`}</strong></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}></td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`-c, --config <path>`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Path the Vector `}<a parentName="td" {...{
              "href": "/docs/setup/configuration/"
            }}>{`configuration file`}</a>{`.`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}></td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}><strong parentName="td">{`Optional`}</strong></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}></td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`-q, --quiet`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Raises the log level to `}<inlineCode parentName="td">{`warn`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}></td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`-qq`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Raises the log level to `}<inlineCode parentName="td">{`error`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}></td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`-qqq`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Turns logging off.`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}></td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`-r, --require-healthy`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Causes vector to immediately exit if any sinks fail their healthchecks.`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}></td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`-t, --threads`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Limits the number of internal threads Vector can spawn.`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}></td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`-v, --verbose`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Drops the log level to `}<inlineCode parentName="td">{`debug`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}></td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`-vv`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Drops the log level to `}<inlineCode parentName="td">{`trace`}</inlineCode>{`, the lowest level possible.`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}></td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`-w, --watch-config`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Vector will watch for changes in `}<a parentName="td" {...{
              "href": "/docs/setup/configuration/"
            }}>{`configuration file`}</a>{`, and reload accordingly. (Mac/Linux only)`}</td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "daemonizing"
    }}>{`Daemonizing`}</h3>
    <p>{`Vector does not `}<em parentName="p">{`directly`}</em>{` offer a way to daemonize the Vector process. We
highly recommend that you use a utility like `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://systemd.io/"
      }}>{`Systemd`}</a>{` to
daemonize and manage your processes. Vector provides a
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://github.com/timberio/vector/blob/master/distribution/systemd/vector.service"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`vector.service`}</inlineCode>{` file`}</a>{` for Systemd.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "stopping"
    }}>{`Stopping`}</h2>
    <p>{`The Vector process can be stopped by sending it a `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`SIGTERM`}</inlineCode>{` process signal:`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "command-1"
    }}>{`Command`}</h3>
    <Tabs block={false} centered={true} groupId="interfaces" placeholder="How did you install Vector?" select={true} size={null} values={[{
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "DPKG",
      "value": "dpkg"
    }, {
      "group": "Platforms",
      "label": "Docker CLI",
      "value": "docker-cli"
    }, {
      "group": "Platforms",
      "label": "Docker Compose",
      "value": "docker-compose"
    }, {
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "Homebrew",
      "value": "homebrew"
    }, {
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "MSI",
      "value": "msi"
    }, {
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "Nix",
      "value": "nix"
    }, {
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "RPM",
      "value": "rpm"
    }, {
      "group": "Nones",
      "label": "Vector CLI",
      "value": "vector-cli"
    }]} mdxType="Tabs">
      <TabItem value="dpkg" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{`sudo systemctl stop vector
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="docker-cli" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{`docker stop timberio/vector
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="docker-compose" mdxType="TabItem">
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="homebrew" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{`brew services stop vector
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="msi" mdxType="TabItem">
        <p>{`The Vector MSI package does not install Vector into a process manager.
Therefore, you are responsible for stopping Vector based on how you started it.`}</p>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="nix" mdxType="TabItem">
        <p>{`The Vector Nix package does not install Vector into a process manager.
Therefore, you are responsible for stopping Vector based on how you started it.`}</p>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="rpm" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{`sudo systemctl stop vector
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="vector-cli" mdxType="TabItem">
        <p>{`If you are starting Vector directly from the Vector CLI then you are responsible
for stopping Vector depending on how you are managing the process. If you're
in the terminal, hitting `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`ctrl+c`}</inlineCode>{` will exit the process.`}</p>
      </TabItem>
    </Tabs>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "graceful-shutdown"
    }}>{`Graceful Shutdown`}</h3>
    <p>{`Vector is designed to gracefully shutdown within 20 seconds when a `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`SIGTERM`}</inlineCode>{`
process signal is received. The shutdown process is as follows:`}</p>
    <ol>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Stop accepting new data for all `}<a parentName="li" {...{
          "href": "/docs/reference/sources/"
        }}>{`sources`}</a>{`.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Gracefully close any open connections with a 20 second timeout.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Flush any sink buffers with a 20 second timeout.`}</li>
      <li parentName="ol">{`Exit the process with a 1 code.`}</li>
    </ol>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "force-killing"
    }}>{`Force Killing`}</h3>
    <p>{`If Vector is forcefully killed there is potential for losing any in-flight
data. To mitigate this we recommend enabling on-disk buffers and avoiding
forceful shutdowns whenever possible.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "exit-codes"
    }}>{`Exit Codes`}</h3>
    <p>{`If Vector fails to start it will exit with one of the preferred exit codes
as defined by `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`sysexits.h`}</inlineCode>{`. A full list of exit codes can be found in the
`}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://docs.rs/exitcode/1.1.2/exitcode/#constants"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`exitcodes`}</inlineCode>{` Rust crate`}</a>{`. The relevant codes that Vector uses
are:`}</p>
    <table>
      <thead parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="thead">
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Code`}</th>
          <th parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Description`}</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody parentName="table">
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`0`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`No error.`}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr parentName="tbody">
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="td">{`78`}</inlineCode></td>
          <td parentName="tr" {...{
            "align": "left"
          }}>{`Bad `}<a parentName="td" {...{
              "href": "/docs/setup/configuration/"
            }}>{`configuration`}</a>{`.`}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "reloading"
    }}>{`Reloading`}</h2>
    <p>{`Vector can be reloaded, on the fly, to recognize any configuration changes by
sending the Vector process a `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`SIGHUP`}</inlineCode>{` signal.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "command-2"
    }}>{`Command`}</h3>
    <Tabs block={false} centered={true} groupId="interfaces" placeholder="How did you install Vector?" select={true} size={null} values={[{
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "DPKG",
      "value": "dpkg"
    }, {
      "group": "Platforms",
      "label": "Docker CLI",
      "value": "docker-cli"
    }, {
      "group": "Platforms",
      "label": "Docker Compose",
      "value": "docker-compose"
    }, {
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "Homebrew",
      "value": "homebrew"
    }, {
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "MSI",
      "value": "msi"
    }, {
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "Nix",
      "value": "nix"
    }, {
      "group": "Package managers",
      "label": "RPM",
      "value": "rpm"
    }, {
      "group": "Nones",
      "label": "Vector CLI",
      "value": "vector-cli"
    }]} mdxType="Tabs">
      <TabItem value="dpkg" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{`sudo systemctl stop vector
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="docker-cli" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{`docker stop timberio/vector
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="docker-compose" mdxType="TabItem">
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="homebrew" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{`brew services stop vector
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="msi" mdxType="TabItem">
        <p>{`The Vector MSI package does not install Vector into a process manager.
Therefore, you are responsible for stopping Vector based on how you started it.`}</p>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="nix" mdxType="TabItem">
        <p>{`The Vector Nix package does not install Vector into a process manager.
Therefore, you are responsible for stopping Vector based on how you started it.`}</p>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="rpm" mdxType="TabItem">
        <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
            "className": "language-bash"
          }}>{`sudo systemctl stop vector
`}</code></pre>
      </TabItem>
      <TabItem value="vector-cli" mdxType="TabItem">
        <p>{`If you are starting Vector directly from the Vector CLI then you are responsible
for stopping Vector depending on how you are managing the process. If you're
in the terminal, hitting `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`ctrl+c`}</inlineCode>{` will exit the process.`}</p>
      </TabItem>
    </Tabs>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "automatic-reload-on-changes"
    }}>{`Automatic Reload On Changes`}</h3>
    <p>{`You can automatically reload Vector's configuration file when it changes via
the `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`-w`}</inlineCode>{` or `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`--watch-config`}</inlineCode>{` flag upon `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "#starting"
      }}>{`starting`}</a>{`. This is
particularly helpful in scenarios where configuration is managed for you, such
as Kubernetes.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "configuration-errors"
    }}>{`Configuration Errors`}</h3>
    <p>{`When Vector is reloaded it proceeds to read the new configuration file from
disk. If the file has errors it will be logged to `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`STDOUT`}</inlineCode>{` and ignored,
preserving any previous configuration that was set. If the process exits you
will not be able to restart the process since it will proceed to use the
new configuration file.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "graceful-pipeline-transitioning"
    }}>{`Graceful Pipeline Transitioning`}</h3>
    <p>{`Vector will perform a diff between the new and old configuration, determining
which sinks and sources should be started and shutdown and ensures the
transition from the old to new pipeline is graceful.`}</p>
    </MDXLayout>;
}

